  "doc_id": "55042",
  "text": "Disadvantages of the virtual reality simulators include maintenance, three dimensions are not always well simulated, haptic feedback often lacks realism, and acceptance by trainees is often low [CITATION_1] . As a result, trainees' focus and effort on the tasks may be minimal. It then becomes less effective as a training tool and is not an accurate representation of actual laparoscopic skill. They are also extremely expensive compared to the video trainers, with the average cost of a virtual simulator ranging from approximately $80,000 to $120,000. That does not include the maintenance fees, technical support, or the purchase of any additional modules for the machine.",
  "correct_citation": {
